  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you cast a spell that has a visible effect, you can spend 2 sorcery points to select a number of affected creatures up to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one creature). To select a creature, it must have failed its saving throw against the spell (if the spell required a saving throw).</p>\n<p>For the next minute, the selected creatures are frightened of you. At the end of each of its turns, the creature can make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC, ending the condition on itself on a success. The condition ends early if you or your allies damage the creature or cast another spell that targets it.</p>",
